         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Monday. ¶  ¶ Just received your letter, dear Mr Shillinglaw, and am very sorry to hear of your troubles. I had no idea, that difficulties could arise to you in this way after your long and useful care...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.09.26b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Shillinglaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Box 243/1, Shillinglaw papers, La Trobe Manuscript Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Shillinglaw’s letter (not found) to which this is the reply was evidently in response to M to J. Shillinglaw, 20 September 1892. There were three Mondays between that letter and M’s Columbus Jubilee Oration at the Melbourne Town Hall on 12 October 1892, mentioned in the postscript. Given the urgency expressed in M’s initial request for help, September 26 is more likely than 3 or 10 of October.</p>
               </note>Monday.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Just received your letter, dear Mr Shillinglaw, and am very sorry to hear of your troubles. I had no idea, that difficulties could arise to you in this way after your long and useful career. Let me trust, that all will be right in the end.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Shillinglaw's troubles not identified.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Pray, do under these sad circumstances not trouble about the Columbus-festival. I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">have</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a lot of thing already, so will not worry you.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
